subSubSection.paragraph:
(=
Sphex maxillosus
of authors before 1976,
S. rufocinctus
of authors after 1975)

N o t e
Sphex funerarius
varies over its extensive range, both in female and male color and number of male antennal placoids. Some females especially can be difficult to distinguish from
S. oxianus
and
S. flavipennis .
Males are easiest to identify because most specimens have broad placoids on flagellomeres III-VIII (MENKE & PULAWSKI 2000: 333).
